        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Disable inactive Claude keychain toggle",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n- Add an `isEnabled` gate to provider toggle descriptors and apply it in the shared provider toggle row.\r\n- Disable the Claude “Avoid Keychain prompts” row while global “Disable Keychain access” is enabled.\r\n- Dim disabled provider toggle row text so inactive rows visually match other disabled settings.\r\n- Add descriptor coverage for the Claude keychain toggle disabled state.\r\n\r\n## Why\r\nWhen global Keychain access is disabled, the Claude “Avoid Keychain prompts” setting has no effective runtime behavior: all Keychain access is blocked. The old UI still showed the stored toggle value and made the row look active, which was confusing because users could see an on/off state that did not currently apply.\r\n\r\n## Validation\r\n- `swift test --filter ProviderSettingsDescriptorTests`\r\n- `make check`\r\n\r\n## Screenshot\r\n\r\nAfter change: \r\n<img width=\"510\" height=\"118\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-06-19 at 12 02 24\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0146d7be-bcd1-4fe0-906d-78d5180e1bdb\" />",
